statement:
\emph{Multiple Choice Question: Exactly ONE of the answers provided is
correct. There is no partial credit in this questions.}

A continuous random variable $X$ has a probability density function of
the form

\begin{align*}f(x) = Ax + Bx^2, \quad \text{for} \quad -1 \leq x \leq 1,\end{align*} where $A$
and $B$ are constants. The values of $A$ and $B$ should be

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{i.} $A=1$, $B=1$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{ii.} $A=1$, $B=3/2$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iii.} $A=0$, $B=3/2$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iv.} $A=0$, $B=2/3$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{v.} $A=2$, $B=3$
\end{description}
